2.00	Canterbury_Crusaders	Crusaders (rugby union)	The Crusaders (formerly the Canterbury Crusaders) are a New Zealand professional rugby union team based in Christchurch that competes in the Super Rugby competition. They are the most successful team in Super Rugby history with seven titles . The franchise represents the Buller, Canterbury, Mid-Canterbury, South Canterbury, Tasman and West Coast provincial Rugby Unions. Their main home ground is AMI Stadium,n 1 formerly known as Jade Stadium and before that, Lancaster Park.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/a9/Canterbury_crusaders.jpg/220px-Canterbury_crusaders.jpg
